Responsibilities:
Carry out survey / start-ups / troubleshooting / guide installation independently onboard vessels / barges and provide timely and accurate reports as per the required standards.
Perform training for customer as well as new service engineers and system operators, produce training materials in cooperation with Flow Training Manager.
Take responsibility of effectively communicating with customers.
Read and interpret electrical circuit diagrams and P&IDs and carry out terminations / tests as required.
Able to sketch isometric drawing of existing pipe routings and peripheral equipments.
Requirements:
Degree/Diploma in Engineering with proven work experience in technical service work.
Must be technical and detail oriented.
Willing to travel in the Asia Pacific region.
Electrical Distribution/Control Panel wiring experience.
Good written and verbal communication skills.
Strong problem solving and decision making skills.
Familiarity with marine environment will be an advantage and able to spend 2 to 3 days on board vessels / barges if required.
Specific work conditions: physically demanding work conditions, high travel frequency and sometimes with short notice.